Fix 7 critical learning system bugs — verification loop now works

The learning system was collecting data but never actually learning
from its mistakes. These fixes unlock the full predict-verify-learn
loop on both server and client.

1. SERVER VERIFICATION FIX: loadRecentPredictions now attaches
   timestamp and predictionHour to each prediction when flattening.
   Previously timestamp was undefined so age filter always failed
   and zero predictions were ever verified.

2. SPEED BIAS FIX: verifyPredictions now computes expectedSpeedMid
   from the [min,max] range. Previously updateWeights could never
   update speed bias because this field was missing.

3. HOURLY BIAS FIX: Uses predictionHour (when the prediction was
   made) instead of verification timestamp hour. A prediction made
   at 8 AM should bias hour 8, not hour 12 when verified.

4. WIND EVENT PATTERN KEYS: WindEventPredictor now looks up learned
   patterns by event type (e.g. "north_flow") in addition to the
   old event_hour format. Also passes through hourlyBias and
   speedBias from server weights during merge.

5. PARAGLIDING IN LEARNING LOOP: DataCollector now records paragliding
   predictions for potm-south and potm-north using predictParagliding().
   Previously paragliding was predicted but never recorded or verified.

6. VERIFICATION VOCABULARY UNIFIED: summarizeActuals now produces a
   windTypes set that maps to all event IDs (e.g. north_flow also
   maps to frontal_passage, post_frontal). calculateAccuracy uses
   fuzzy matching via this set instead of exact string comparison.

7. PER-LOCATION USER FEEDBACK: calculateNewWeights now uses
   locationFeedback data to compute per-spot speed bias corrections,
   stored in locationBias. Previously only aggregate userSpeedBias
   was used while per-location data was thrown away.
